					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/sh85118979" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Pentateuch scroll. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="6r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר תורה</title>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 16th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>89 membranes, 268 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>625</height>
										<width>52410</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>89 membranes, with header/wrapper (813mm). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Slight tidemark at head. Recurrent damp damage with contractions, losses and a dark brittle margin. </p>
									<p>Occasional surface abrasion or delamination, a few deliberate erasures. </p>
									<p>A few pleats slightly obscuring text. </p>
									<p>Numerous edge tears and wear.</p>
									<p>A few old repairs, with losses. </p>
									<p>Usage stains, slight mould spots and a few areas with liquid trickles.  </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="268" ruledLines="45" writtenLines="45">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and stitching. </p>
									<p>268 columns in total, two to four columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on the letters שעטנזגץ, and one on the letters בדהחיק. </p>
									<p>Numbers 13:1-20 is written in smaller letters. </p>
									<p>Special arrangement of lines of the Song of Moses, Ex. 15. The Song Ha&apos;azinu, Deut. 32, is written in 70 lines. The Song is followed by verses 44-47 arranged in seven lines. The first דרש of Lev. 10:16 is written at the end of the line. Puncta extraordinaria placed only on some of the words fixed by the masorah. </p>
									<p>Majuscular and minuscular letters occur. </p>
									<p>The inverted letter nun is placed before and after Num. 10:35-36. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
